# StudyOS First Live Runtime Proof

Date: 2026-04-19

## Commands

```bash
STUDYOS_CODEX_AVAILABLE=1 cargo test -p studyos-cli --test runtime_live -- --ignored --nocapture
cargo run -p studyos-cli --example record_runtime_session
```

## Live runtime smoke test

```text
running 2 tests
test runtime_live_reaches_first_question ... ok
test runtime_live_completes_submission_round_trip ... ok

test result: ok. 2 passed; 0 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 45.37s
```

What this proves:

- StudyOS can spawn a real local `codex app-server`.
- The opening turn reaches a tutor-generated structured question.
- A structured submission can be sent back through the live runtime.
- The graded response is parsed and persisted to SQLite as attempt evidence.

